name: Python Flask for Newbies Codelab

venue.name: Techverse
venue.address_1: Appartment 9, 5th floor, Building 9, Rue Ksar e Souk, Rue Al-Mariniyine, Hassan, 11000 Rabat, Morocco

description:
Python Flask for newbies ─ Codelab

Audience: beginners in python, knowledge of any programming language. 

 
Content: this will be a hands-on workshop to discover Flask python, we will together build an API for our app, and host it to the cloud. 

 
If you are new to python don’t worry this will be a very good introduction to how easy and fast you can learn python.
Bonus: if we advance in the workshop quickly we can take our code to a RaspberryPI and play around with it.

Prerequisites: You will need your laptop with preferably Linux machine, or with python installed on your windows or max, please follow this link to get ready for the workshop.

Duration: 2 hours.

Don't forget to RSVP - see you there.

Spots are very limited. You will be emailed a RSVP form in the next few days.

name: Firebase workshop #1

venue.name: Techverse
venue.address_1: Appartment 9, 5th floor, Building 9, Rue Ksar e Souk, Rue Al-Mariniyine, Hassan, 11000 Rabat, Morocco

description:
Hello there, Come join us and Learn how to use the Firebase platform to empower you to deploy sophisticated web and mobile applications without having to build your own complex, server-side infrastructure. Firebase provides a database that sends updates to the client-side application in real-time, caches requests when there is network latency or no connection, offers conflict resolution, and allows you to define custom access rules.Additionally, Firebase offers easy authentication, hosting, storage, and message. In this workshop, we'll learn about this and more!

Your instructors:
Ahmed Amine Hachimi &
Khyatti Reda &
Zakariae Mâzoûzi
